task.summary: Default task
Created a graph_controller class, which is currently a stub. Creates a drawing area and if this file was called, a window will be created and shown (i.e this file can be run standalone).
Creating a class which can import the camkes file, run the parser and get an LiftedAST object
Creating a class which can import the camkes file, run the parser and get an LiftedAST object
Removed unnecessary README files and added __init__ files so that each file could be imported in other files.
Created a AST_Widget base class
Created an AST_creator object which will use the appropriate parser (or in the future parser to a certain stage).
Did some rearranging and attempting to create a AST_widget + draw onto the screen
Added Lazy Instantiation to root_widget
Created an AST_Widget. Useless atm

Using graphviz to create a DOT graph representation of the AST tree. Then using this to get positions of each node (each instance). Using glade and Gtk.Builder to build custom UI for each instance. Create a list of widget_builder for each instance.
Using AST_Widget to test out drawing lines. Failed attempt :(. This class won't (should be) used anyway.
Created a widget to represent connections. Currently doesn't work. Finding it difficult to draw a line between two other widgets. Will have to figure out a way in Milestone 3
Created a widget to represent an Instance.

Added code that would go through an AST Tree, make instance widgets and add them on the screen. A render function will then be immediately called. The render function will create a new graph (using graphviz), add nodes (and their sizes) to the graph, add connections as well, and use the final positions in the graph to display them on the root_widget (Gtk.Layout)
Added glade, and builder files for quick and dirty instance widgets
Added stuff about Milestone 2 to readme
Updated read me with more ideas and features
Instance Widget subclasses QFrame and shows instance's name with component type
Created a Widget class which will add widgets on a "canvas", and add connections.
Subclasses QWidget and draws a line given by graphviz
Added a common file with common functions
Uses GraphWidget, adds instance widgets to graphs, uses graphviz to lay out components and connections, and successfully shows something on the screen
Able to handle scientific notation numbers
Added a component window to display component info in a new window, and in the future as a side panel item.
Changed the way ui is refreshed. Ability to get a signal from Instance_Widget to open a component_window. Component_window stored in GraphController
